  |- wf(c0, cxp(c1, c2o), cxp(c1, c2o))
  -| wceq(c0, cmpo(s0, s1, c1, c2o, cop(cv(s0), cdif(c1o, cv(s1)))))

  -| diffsc(s0, c1)
  -| diffsc(s1, c1)
} = {
  mpbi(wf(c0, cxp(c1, c2o), cxp(c1, c2o)), wral(s0, c1, wral(s1, c2o, wcel(cop(cv(s0), cdif(c1o, cv(s1))), cxp(c1, c2o)))))
  rgen2(s0, s1, c1, c2o, wcel(cop(cv(s0), cdif(c1o, cv(s1))), cxp(c1, c2o)))
  sylan2(wcel(cv(s0), c1), wcel(cv(s1), c2o), wcel(cop(cv(s0), cdif(c1o, cv(s1))), cxp(c1, c2o)), wcel(cdif(c1o, cv(s1)), c2o))
  2oconcl(cv(s1))
  opelxpi(cv(s0), c1, cdif(c1o, cv(s1)), c2o)
  fmpt2(s0, s1, c1, c2o, cop(cv(s0), cdif(c1o, cv(s1))), cxp(c1, c2o), c0)
  diff.cxp.s(s0, c1, c2o)
  diff.c2o.s(s0)
  diff.cxp.s(s1, c1, c2o)
  diff.c2o.s(s1)
}

  elxp2(hs0, hs1, c0, c1, c2o)
  rexlimivv(hs0, hs1, c1, c2o, wceq(c0, cop(cv(hs0), cv(hs1))), wceq(cfv(c2, cfv(c2, c0)), c0))
  syl5ibrcom(wa(wcel(cv(hs0), c1), wcel(cv(hs1), c2o)), wceq(c0, cop(cv(hs0), cv(hs1))), wceq(cfv(c2, cfv(c2, c0)), c0), wceq(cfv(c2, co(cv(hs0), c2, cv(hs1))), cop(cv(hs0), cv(hs1))))
  3eqtrd(cfv(c2, co(cv(hs0), c2, cv(hs1))), cop(cv(hs0), cv(hs1)), co(cv(hs0), c2, cdif(c1o, cv(hs1))), cop(cv(hs0), cdif(c1o, cdif(c1o, cv(hs1)))), wa(wcel(cv(hs0), c1), wcel(cv(hs1), c2o)))
  syl6eqr(cfv(c2, co(cv(hs0), c2, cv(hs1))), co(cv(hs0), c2, cdif(c1o, cv(hs1))), cfv(c2, cop(cv(hs0), cdif(c1o, cv(hs1)))), wa(wcel(cv(hs0), c1), wcel(cv(hs1), c2o)))
  fveq2d(c2, co(cv(hs0), c2, cv(hs1)), cop(cv(hs0), cdif(c1o, cv(hs1))), wa(wcel(cv(hs0), c1), wcel(cv(hs1), c2o)))
  efgmval(s0, s1, cv(hs0), c1, cv(hs1), c2)
  df-ov(cv(hs0), c2, cdif(c1o, cv(hs1)))
  sylan2(wcel(cv(hs0), c1), wcel(cv(hs1), c2o), wceq(co(cv(hs0), c2, cdif(c1o, cv(hs1))), cop(cv(hs0), cdif(c1o, cdif(c1o, cv(hs1))))), wcel(cdif(c1o, cv(hs1)), c2o))
  2oconcl(cv(hs1))
  efgmval(s0, s1, cv(hs0), c1, cdif(c1o, cv(hs1)), c2)
  opeq2d(cv(hs0), cdif(c1o, cdif(c1o, cv(hs1))), cv(hs1), wa(wcel(cv(hs0), c1), wcel(cv(hs1), c2o)))
  sylib(wa(wcel(cv(hs0), c1), wcel(cv(hs1), c2o)), wceq(cdif(c1o, cdif(c1o, cv(hs1))), cv(hs1)), wss(cv(hs1), c1o))
  adantl(wcel(cv(hs0), c1), wcel(cv(hs1), c2o), wss(cv(hs1), c1o))
  eleq2s(cv(hs1), c2o, csuc(c1o), wss(cv(hs1), c1o))
  mp2b(wi(wcel(cv(hs1), csuc(c1o)), wss(cv(hs1), c1o)), word(c1o), wtr(c1o))

  dfss4(cv(hs1), c1o)

  fveq2d(c2, cfv(c2, c0), co(cv(hs0), c2, cv(hs1)), wceq(c0, cop(cv(hs0), cv(hs1))))
  syl6eqr(cfv(c2, c0), co(cv(hs0), c2, cv(hs1)), cfv(c2, cop(cv(hs0), cv(hs1))), wceq(c0, cop(cv(hs0), cv(hs1))))
  fveq2(c0, cop(cv(hs0), cv(hs1)), c2)

blocks.content: Lemma for ~ efgval . (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 1-Oct-2015.) (Revised by Mario Carneiro, 27-Feb-2016.)

thm efgrcl(class c0, class c1, class c2) {
  |- wi(wcel(c0, c1), wa(wcel(c2, universe), wceq(c1, cword(cxp(c2, c2o)))))
  -| wceq(c1, cfv(cid, cword(cxp(c2, c2o))))
} = {
  jca(wcel(c0, c1), wcel(c2, universe), wceq(c1, cword(cxp(c2, c2o))))
  syl5eqelr(c2, universe, cdm(cxp(c2, c2o)), wcel(c0, c1))
  ax-mp(wceq(cdm(cxp(c2, c2o)), c2), wne(c2o, emptycls))
  2on0()

blocks.name: efgsfo
blocks.content: For any word, there is a sequence of extensions starting at a reduced word and ending at the target word, such that each word in the chain is an extension of the previous (inserting an element and its inverse at adjacent indices somewhere in the sequence). (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 27-Sep-2015.)

blocks.name: efgrelexlema
blocks.content: If two words ` A , B ` are related under the free group equivalence, then there exist two extension sequences ` a , b ` such that ` a ` ends at ` A ` , ` b ` ends at ` B ` , and ` a ` and ` B ` have the same starting point. (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 1-Oct-2015.)

blocks.name: efgrelexlemb
blocks.content: If two words ` A , B ` are related under the free group equivalence, then there exist two extension sequences ` a , b ` such that ` a ` ends at ` A ` , ` b ` ends at ` B ` , and ` a ` and ` B ` have the same starting point. (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 1-Oct-2015.)

blocks.name: efgrelex
blocks.content: If two words ` A , B ` are related under the free group equivalence, then there exist two extension sequences ` a , b ` such that ` a ` ends at ` A ` , ` b ` ends at ` B ` , and ` a ` and ` B ` have the same starting point. (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 1-Oct-2015.)

blocks.name: frgpupf
blocks.content: Any assignment of the generators to target elements can be extended (uniquely) to a homomorphism from a free monoid to an arbitrary other monoid. (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 2-Oct-2015.)
